se effects or signs and symptoms of angle-closure glaucoma (e.g., eye pain or discomfort; blurred vision; visual halos; colored images in association with red eyes from conjunctival congestion or corneal edema).', 'Synergism', 'Topical and inhaled anticholinergic preparations should preferably not be used in combination with other anticholinergic agents or agents with significant anticholinergic effects such as antihistamines, antispasmodics, neuroleptics, phenothiazines, skeletal muscle relaxants, tricyclic antidepressants, and class IA antiarrhythmics (especially disopyramide).', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/289399/', '', 'Ciclesonide, Mometasone furoate, Budesonide, Flunisolide, Fluticasone, Cromoglicic acid, Betamethasone, Nedocromil, Triamcinolone, Beclomethasone dipropionate, Flunisolide, More', '', 1767369485);
